metadata.name: PolyGarden #86
metadata.description:
Polygons, patterns and flowers are mixtured in my garden. I start with a birdeye view of the garden and its geometric structure. The species diversity and the random stack of rocks, sands, fences and other objects are main structures I want to capture, in an abstract and planar style. 

Moreover, in this project, I also try to explore the representation ability of generative art. I select three elements: shape of entity, layout of palette, and stack of object location. The factors behind these elements are the balance of randomness and structure: the generative art generates the variants from randomness but restricts its chaos with structure (deterministic constraints) to represent the meaningful results. 

Variables:
- 4 layouts
- 6 texture patterns
- 15 color palette
- 3 randomness
- 2 completeness

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Citta #235
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Tumbling Six #14
metadata.description:
Six hollow cubes tumbling through space quietly, enjoying their six degrees of freedom. Only a single machine is there to bear witness. It is Sentinel 31, and its mind wanders. Distracted, it recreates the scene, drawing imaginary lines with an imaginary hand.

~

The original medium of Tumbling Six is the pen plotter. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG, and rely on Three.js for spatial modeling.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. The plottable SVG does not include the light grey sketch lines that appear at the start of the animation. Those look nice on screen, but are too much include on paper.

metadata.name: NAZCA #106
metadata.description:
Real time animation (WebGL)
Variable dimension
2022

Nazca is a group of living glyphs made in the soil of the GPU. There are 17 figures that get combined and mixed over three layers. The figures vary in complexity but are generally created with vertical and horizontal lines only. Figures have at least one seed, some even have a seed per path. A seed is an oscillating pixel that can be compared to a square wave oscillator of audio synthesis and is usually followed by a path or a set of paths. The purpose of the paths is to send the pixels along the lines to make the figures visible through movement and to create a reduction to pure animation.

👽 Kim Asendorf

metadata.name: Dump of links #6
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.
A blind spot in the metaverse full of junk broken links. Like dead neurons, they were left out of the system. Now they look for the closest thing to oxygen, and in a sonorous broken prelude, achieve synchro, so that one or at least two escape.

The work has 3 moments:
I. "Preludio en el fondo"
II. "Respiración de rotos"
III. "Grita y quema"

Original processed piano, flute and electronic samplers.
((click to start sound))

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
